class="mpci-1ustk6r eu4oa1w0"><div class="mpci-14461mr eu4oa1w0"></div></div></div></div></div><div id="benefits" class="jobsearch-JobDescriptionSection-section css-1pza7cr eu4oa1w0"><h2 class="jobsearch-JobDescriptionSection-jobDescriptionTitle">Benefits<div class="css-brixrz e1wnkr790">Pulled from the full job description</div></h2><div class="css-4l8g94 eu4oa1w0"><div class="css-k3ey05 eu4oa1w0"><div class="css-1f2yqp0 e1xnxm2i0"><div class="css-g6kqeb ecydgvn0"><div class="css-tvvxwd ecydgvn1">Dental insurance</div></div></div><div class="css-1f2yqp0 e1xnxm2i0"><div class="css-g6kqeb ecydgvn0"><div class="css-tvvxwd ecydgvn1">Health insurance</div></div></div><div class="css-1f2yqp0 e1xnxm2i0"><div class="css-g6kqeb ecydgvn0"><div class="css-tvvxwd ecydgvn1">Vision insurance</div></div></div></div></div></div><h2 id="jobDescriptionTitle" class="jobsearch-JobDescriptionSection-jobDescriptionTitle icl-u-xs-my--md">Full Job Description</h2><div id="jobDescriptionText" class="jobsearch-jobDescriptionText"><p><b>Sr. Data Analyst</b></p>
<p><b>6 Month Contract</b></p>
<p><b>Pay Rate: $40 - $44/hr</b></p>
<p>The Global RFID program is responsible for building the framework and roadmap for RFID technology in the Company’s O&amp;O fleet of retail stores. We are seeking an RFID Professional to collaborate with global partners to identify and define new capabilities for implementation in our stores. This individual should be self-motivated and comfortable with building process or system from the ground up. -</p>
<p><b>Essential Duties and Responsibilities</b></p>
<ul>
 <li>Responsible for gathering functional data requirements and translating them to technical requirements.</li>
 <li>Performing analytics on program metrics/activities</li>
 <li>Own routine report share-outs to Field/Leadership teams.</li>
 <li>Ideate ways in which RFID technology, or other solutions, can support or improve current state</li>
 <li>Identify and develop data models to monitor hypotheses and KPIs</li>
 <li>Regular communication with global teammates</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Skills and Qualifications</b></p>
<ul>
 <li>Proficient in Requirements Gathering and Report Creation, Tableau Experience is a plus</li>
 <li>Familiar with SQL and Snowflake</li>
 <li>Retail or Inventory knowledge/experience is desired</li>
 <li>Solutions Oriented</li>
 <li>Analytical and data minded individuals.</li>
 <li>Strong oral and written communication skills, strong collaborator</li>
 <li>Effectively self-manage time and tasks</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Other Requirements: </b></p>
<ul>
 <li>Remote but able to flex hours as there will expectation to collaborate with global partners</li>
 <li>Travel (5-15% depending on location</li>
</ul>
<p>Job Type: Contract</p>
<p>Pay: $40.00 - $44.00 per hour</p>
<p>Benefits:</p>
<ul>
 <li>Dental insurance</li>
 <li>Health insurance</li>
 <li>Vision insurance</li>
</ul>
<p>Schedule:</p>
<ul>
 <li>8 hour shift</li>
 <li>Monday to Friday</li>
</ul>
<p>Experience:</p>
<ul>
 <li>SQL: 1 year (Required)</li>
 <li>Snowflake: 1 year (Required)</li>
 <li>Tableau: 1 year (Required)</li>
 <li>Retail or Inventory knowledge: 1 year (Required)</li>
</ul>
<p>Work Location: Remote</p></div><div id="belowFullJobDescription" class="mosaic mosaic-empty-zone"></div><div id="hiringInsightsSectionRoot" class="jobsearch-HiringInsights-root     function loadScript() {
        if (!window.gtag) {
            var script = document.createElement('script');
            var done = false;
            var head = document.getElementsByTagName("head")[0];
            script.src = 'https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=DC-' + '6927552';
            script.onload = script.onreadystatechange = function(){
                if ( !done && (!this.readyState || this.readyState == "loaded" || this.readyState == "complete") ) {
                    done = true;
                    configureGtag();
                    // IE memory leak
                    script.onload = script.onreadystatechange = null;
                    head.removeChild( script );
                }
            };
            head.appendChild(script);
        }
    }
    function configureGtag() {
